-- Germans Youths on Welfare Dropped 13.5%, Sueddeutsche Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-01-26T07:21:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/germans-youths-on-welfare-dropped-13-5-sueddeutsche-reports.html
The number of Germans under 15
receiving social welfare has declined by 13.5 percent in the
past five years to 1.64 million,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported
today, citing a Federal Employment Agency report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
